learnItems.back:
- you use the **descendant combinator**, styles separated by spaces
	-----------------------------------
	ul {
		list-style-type: circle;
	}

	ul ul {
		list-style-type: disc;
	}
	-----------------------------------

- you can change the color slightly on mouseover, e.g.
	---------------------------------------
	button.normal {
		background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
		color: #ccc;
		padding: 1rem;
	}

	button.normal:hover {
		background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
	}	
	---------------------------------------
	- this works like this:#gif#theoverbutton
- you can give opacity to the hover of an image, e.g.
	------------------------------------------------
	#content img {
		width: 100px;
	}

	#content img:hover {
		opacity: 0.8;
	}
	------------------------------------------------
	- this works like this:#gif#thetwopicsjo
